    "claim": "Liquidity/shortfall checks read `exchangeRateStored()` and `borrowIndex()` for every supplied/borrowed market without accruing those markets first, while call sites accrue only one market (or none), so collateral/debt can be materially stale during authorization and liquidation decisions.",
    "impact": "Users can borrow or redeem against understated liabilities, and liquidation eligibility can be evaluated on stale collateral/debt, causing insolvency risk and wrongful liquidations.",
    "paths": [
      "Build debt in market A, let A remain unaccrued, then borrow in market B; the borrow check underestimates debt from A.",
      "Let collateral market C remain unaccrued, then trigger liquidation on debt market D; stale C exchange rate can make a solvent account appear liquidatable."
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "F-047",
    "severity": "Medium",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "title": "Cross-chain liquidation accepts unmapped seize markets and can emit unprocessable packets",
    "locations": [
      "LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:197",
      "LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:280",
      "LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:326",
      "LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:479"
    ],
    "claim": "`liquidateCrossChain` never validates that `lTokenToSeize` has a valid `crossChainLTokenMap` entry for `srcEid`; `_executeLiquidationCore` forwards the mapping result directly, and receive-side handlers assume `payload.destlToken` is valid market/token identity.",
    "impact": "A caller can craft liquidation requests that deterministically revert on the remote handler (e.g., invalid market/token handling), producing stuck retry packets and cross-chain DoS on that message lane.",
    "paths": [
      "Call `liquidateCrossChain` with a listed local collateral market that has no source-chain mapping.",
      "Packet carries invalid `destlToken`; remote liquidation/failure handler reverts repeatedly."
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "F-048",
    "severity": "Medium",
    "confidence": "low",
    "title": "Liquidation seize quantity is computed in one chain domain and enforced in another",
    "locations": [
      "LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:268",
      "LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:280",
      "LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:333"
    ],
    "claim": "`seizeTokens` is calculated using debt-chain market parameters (`liquidateCalculateSeizeTokens` on local `lTokenToSeize`) and then applied as a raw token quantity to mapped source-chain collateral, without re-quoting in the source-chain market domain.",
    "impact": "When cross-chain oracle/exchange-rate domains diverge, liquidation can over-seize or under-seize collateral, creating unfair borrower loss or residual bad debt.",
